  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "While oficcially [we only support LTS versions of node.js](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/reference/stability-guarantees#node.js-versions-support), non-LTS versions are likely to work. But sometimes users can't use some of these versions (see #3341) because we have a strict list of engines in our `package.json`.\r\n\r\nWe should:\r\n- [x] Drop the engines field from the `package.json`, or change it to something more permissive like `>=10.0.0` (I'm not sure about the trade-offs here)\r\n- [x] Print a warning when a non-supported version is used (see [this comment](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/3341#issuecomment-1322529104) for an important implementation detail).",
